===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}}, differentiated form of {{och-l|夗}}, which was originally the same character. 

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' suggests that it is an {{liushu|i|nocap=1}} from flipped {{zh-l|*仄|to tilt}} – something that can be tilted and turned; something round.

Unrelated to the right component of characters like {{zh-l|*執}} and {{zh-l|*孰}}, which comes from {{zh-l|*丮}} (a kneeling person with stretched arms to indicate "to hold").

